1
00:00:00,260 --> 00:00:02,920
[Would you like to join Spirit Fingers?]

2
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:25,512
♫ A heart that remains
unchanged through time ♫

3
00:00:25,536 --> 00:00:31,179
♫ Our eternal story
that will last forever ♫

4
00:00:35,616 --> 00:00:37,352
[This drama is fictional, and any similarity
with reality is purely coincidental.]

5
00:00:37,376 --> 00:00:40,216
[Production guidelines were followed
when filming children and animals.]

6
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,580
Do you like Seon Ho?

7
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:49,740
I'm asking if you like him?

8
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,640
You like him.

9
00:01:12,448 --> 00:01:16,660
[Episode 3] Ugh! What is this feeling?

10
00:01:18,960 --> 00:01:20,872
Do you like Seon Ho?

11
00:01:20,896 --> 00:01:24,096
What am I supposed to do?

12
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:25,940
Why can't you say it?

13
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,486
Why can't you say it?

14
00:01:29,510 --> 00:01:30,606
"I like him."

15
00:01:30,630 --> 00:01:31,636
"He's my soulmate."

16
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:33,576
Why can't you say it?

17
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,856
Did I do something wrong again?

18
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:37,690
- Should I have told him?
- Are you crazy?

19
00:01:37,714 --> 00:01:39,404
You did well this time.

20
00:01:39,428 --> 00:01:42,387
- Your shyness and lameness saved you.
- What?

21
00:01:42,411 --> 00:01:45,107
What are you staring at? You already know.

22
00:01:45,131 --> 00:01:46,741
If you admit it,

23
00:01:46,765 --> 00:01:49,337
it's only a matter of time
before Seon Ho finds out.

24
00:01:50,537 --> 00:01:55,206
- He's not the type to tell.
- No, he isn't.

25
00:01:55,230 --> 00:01:57,806
But you know, even if you can trust
the person, you can't trust the situation.

26
00:01:57,830 --> 00:02:01,748
A situation could arise where he just
blurts it out without realizing it.

27
00:02:04,285 --> 00:02:05,713
Shall we continue our conversation?

28
00:02:05,737 --> 00:02:09,565
Do you hate it or like
it if Seon Ho finds out?

29
00:02:12,060 --> 00:02:14,857
- I hate it.
- Why?

30
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,850
Because I'll definitely get rejected.

31
00:02:19,874 --> 00:02:21,896
Just thinking about it makes me cringe.

32
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:24,205
Shut up, okay?

33
00:02:29,234 --> 00:02:31,100
Okay.

34
00:02:33,645 --> 00:02:36,870
Goodnight, love you.

35
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,820
No way!

36
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,558
How did he know?

37
00:02:48,582 --> 00:02:50,844
Not knowing would've been weird.

38
00:02:50,868 --> 00:02:52,593
It's so obvious.

39
00:02:52,617 --> 00:02:54,126
You must have been giving it away, right?

40
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:56,707
You just saw his face and
smiled like an idiot, didn't you?

41
00:02:56,731 --> 00:02:58,880
Have some pride.

42
00:03:00,468 --> 00:03:02,261
So? What did he say?

43
00:03:02,285 --> 00:03:04,137
No idea.

44
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,636
He just said, 'you like him, ' and left.

45
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,890
Just like that?

46
00:03:08,914 --> 00:03:12,240
What was his tone when
he said, 'you like him'?

47
00:03:13,154 --> 00:03:14,506
Gosh, I can't tell.

48
00:03:14,530 --> 00:03:16,276
I was too shocked.

49
00:03:16,300 --> 00:03:18,571
Like making fun of you?

50
00:03:20,045 --> 00:03:23,308
- Look closely, ta-da!
- You like him.

51
00:03:23,332 --> 00:03:26,948
- Why push me?
- You like him.

52
00:03:28,068 --> 00:03:30,184
You like him.

53
00:03:30,208 --> 00:03:31,244
You like him.

54
00:03:31,268 --> 00:03:33,546
Ugh, it's all mixed up.

55
00:03:33,570 --> 00:03:35,872
Do you like him?

56
00:03:38,848 --> 00:03:40,704
You like him.

57
00:03:41,588 --> 00:03:44,513
But he seemed angry.

58
00:03:44,537 --> 00:03:47,050
- Angry?
- Yeah.

59
00:03:50,868 --> 00:03:52,046
Right, that's it.

60
00:03:52,070 --> 00:03:54,176
Furious, completely pissed off.

61
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:56,250
I heard his sister and
that guy like each other.

62
00:03:56,274 --> 00:03:58,376
No, she said they're just friends.

63
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,227
'Just friends' between a
guy and a girl? Nonsense.

64
00:04:00,251 --> 00:04:01,656
They're clearly flirting.

65
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:04,650
He's mad you might interfere
with his sister's love life.

66
00:04:04,674 --> 00:04:07,244
Even if their sibling chemistry is
fire, his sister matters most.

67
00:04:07,268 --> 00:04:09,280
Why would some random girl matter?

68
00:04:11,348 --> 00:04:15,211
- Right?
- Maybe he's just mad that she likes him.

69
00:04:15,907 --> 00:04:17,553
Gosh.

70
00:04:17,577 --> 00:04:18,924
Dude, I got the chills.

71
00:04:18,948 --> 00:04:22,376
True friends wake you up harshly
when needed, even if it hurts.

72
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,587
Where's the proof that I'm wrong?

73
00:04:23,611 --> 00:04:24,636
It's right here.

74
00:04:24,660 --> 00:04:25,666
Watch carefully again.

75
00:04:25,690 --> 00:04:29,644
Ta-da! Crazy chemistry!

76
00:04:33,066 --> 00:04:35,200
U Yeon.

77
00:04:37,511 --> 00:04:41,596
Nam Gi Jeong! Ta-da! Insane!

78
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:43,836
All three have model vibes.

79
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:46,586
Even if you make that sad
face, it can't be helped.

80
00:04:46,610 --> 00:04:47,756
Chemistry is science.

81
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:49,406
There's no particular reason
for Nam Gi Jeong to like U Yeon,

82
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:51,556
but are there plenty of reasons
for him not to like her?

83
00:04:51,580 --> 00:04:53,316
Isn't it obvious?

84
00:04:53,340 --> 00:04:54,756
- He's a model.
- Hey.

85
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:57,264
We're not talking about
him and me right now.

86
00:04:57,288 --> 00:04:59,911
I was about to get annoyed.

87
00:05:02,820 --> 00:05:04,896
But Mi Rae,

88
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,946
you're right about everything.

89
00:05:06,970 --> 00:05:09,244
I know you're a sharp-shooter,

90
00:05:09,870 --> 00:05:13,955
but sometimes, please,
miss the target a little. Let's go.

91
00:05:15,290 --> 00:05:16,676
Go easy on her.

92
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:19,422
Even if you miss, everyone
knows you're my best friend.

93
00:05:20,044 --> 00:05:22,844
Hey, what did I...

94
00:05:30,610 --> 00:05:32,410
Why did you call me?

95
00:05:38,590 --> 00:05:42,446
Last night... last night

96
00:05:42,470 --> 00:05:45,126
you asked me something weird.

97
00:05:45,150 --> 00:05:47,487
I don't like Seon Ho.

98
00:05:47,511 --> 00:05:50,933
Why ask that out of nowhere?
It made me feel weird.

99
00:05:58,020 --> 00:05:59,956
No, it's just...

100
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:02,656
It's not really something
I need to explain,

101
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:07,887
but since you basically declared
it a fact, got mad and left...

102
00:06:07,911 --> 00:06:09,309
Did I get mad and leave?

103
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:11,131
You seemed mad yesterday.

104
00:06:11,155 --> 00:06:12,731
Why would I be mad?

105
00:06:12,755 --> 00:06:15,353
Why should I care who you
like? Why would I be upset?

106
00:06:15,377 --> 00:06:18,198
I never said you were upset.

107
00:06:18,222 --> 00:06:21,353
Anyway, I was not mad.

108
00:06:21,377 --> 00:06:24,044
Then why did you leave without
even saying goodbye yesterday?

109
00:06:25,066 --> 00:06:27,931
Because... my stomach hurt.

110
00:06:27,955 --> 00:06:31,426
- Don't you know I have IBS?
- I didn't.

111
00:06:31,450 --> 00:06:32,536
Hey, really!

112
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,786
How could you not know that?

113
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:35,076
How did we first meet?

114
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:39,353
If I didn't have that condition, would
I ask a random stranger for tissue?

115
00:06:39,377 --> 00:06:43,586
But if I had that condition,
I would carry tissues around.

116
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:46,331
That's why I never thought you had IBS.

117
00:06:46,355 --> 00:06:50,133
Why are you so smart?

118
00:06:50,977 --> 00:06:54,355
Oh right, you said you're good at studying.

119
00:06:58,490 --> 00:06:59,736
Why are you laughing?

120
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:03,087
It's so weird. Why is everything
so easy when I'm with you?

121
00:07:03,111 --> 00:07:07,377
No matter how serious it is,
it becomes nothing. It's strange.

122
00:07:11,466 --> 00:07:14,488
- Then, I'm relieved.
- Huh?

123
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:21,955
Wait, so you don't like Seon Ho?

124
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:29,536
Yeah, he's just a nice guy.

125
00:07:30,304 --> 00:07:32,296
Got it.

126
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:35,360
I can't make it to this week's gathering
because of my part-time job.

127
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:56,598
You should learn how to lie better, kid.

128
00:07:56,622 --> 00:07:58,686
Not bad, your lying has improved.

129
00:07:58,710 --> 00:08:01,916
- Was it okay?
- You did well.

130
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:05,866
But you hesitated for a beat.

131
00:08:07,170 --> 00:08:11,511
I was worried you'd say you liked Seon Ho.

132
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:16,786
Gi Jeong really needs
to learn how to lie better.

133
00:08:16,810 --> 00:08:19,042
He said he wasn't mad,
but he was totally mad.

134
00:08:19,066 --> 00:08:21,555
This feels like the right thing to say.

135
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:26,186
You did well this time.

136
00:08:26,210 --> 00:08:29,046
Of course, being honest
and confident is the best,

137
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:31,887
but you have to look before you leap.

138
00:08:31,911 --> 00:08:36,356
If you're honest and confident and end up being
teased about it forever, you might want to die.

139
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:39,777
Always put yourself first.

140
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:45,442
Now, go back to how you were.

141
00:08:45,466 --> 00:08:48,420
Keep Seon Ho as your
eternal one-sided love.

142
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:50,386
That's better, right?

143
00:08:50,410 --> 00:08:55,288
The excitement, butterflies
and occasional heart-flutters.

144
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:06,847
[The system is down.]

145
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,706
Let's mourn the death of this assignment.

146
00:09:09,730 --> 00:09:11,670
Ugh, so frustrating!

147
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:16,755
I'm doomed.

148
00:09:18,666 --> 00:09:20,776
This is divine intervention.

149
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,856
How about a beer? Deal?

150
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:25,216
We still have time before the deadline.

151
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:27,306
- Hurry up and start again.
- Yeah.

152
00:09:27,330 --> 00:09:29,606
This is so typical of you.

153
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:33,777
Okay, let's try again.

154
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:38,752
Hey!

155
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,286
- Hey...
- Hey, wait.

156
00:09:42,310 --> 00:09:43,476
Stay still.

157
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:44,796
Am I bleeding?

158
00:09:44,820 --> 00:09:47,087
Luckily, no blood.

159
00:09:47,111 --> 00:09:49,955
Watch where you're going next time.

160
00:09:55,644 --> 00:09:59,911
To me, you're a girl.
That's why it's a problem.

161
00:10:02,816 --> 00:10:10,816
[Koo Seo No, you jerk!]

162
00:10:12,711 --> 00:10:14,977
Hey, Seon Ho.

163
00:10:19,111 --> 00:10:20,509
Coffee delivery is here.

164
00:10:20,533 --> 00:10:22,666
This is my junior from
the first year, Kang Ji Won.

165
00:10:23,330 --> 00:10:25,798
I'm Koo Seon Ho, Geu Rin's friend.

166
00:10:25,822 --> 00:10:29,626
You look even better up close.
Speak casually, please.

167
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:31,816
Don't even mention it. This kid
has been driving me crazy,

168
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:35,346
- saying she wants to get close to you.
- True, I made a scene.

169
00:10:35,370 --> 00:10:38,153
She's such a rare, adorable junior.

170
00:10:38,177 --> 00:10:42,133
Myeong Hun's a great junior too.

171
00:10:42,950 --> 00:10:45,980
I want to be more than a good junior.

172
00:10:46,888 --> 00:10:49,066
Myeong Hun, listen up.

173
00:10:49,090 --> 00:10:50,716
There's no room for 'good men' in my life.

174
00:10:50,740 --> 00:10:53,746
Only good friends, brothers, and juniors.

175
00:10:53,770 --> 00:10:55,936
If you can't keep
boundaries, I will. Don't worry.

176
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:58,316
Wow, you're such a girl crush.

177
00:10:58,340 --> 00:11:00,336
It's not like boundaries are visible.

178
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,626
How can you stick to it perfectly?

179
00:11:01,650 --> 00:11:04,820
Hey, if I tell you to stick to it,
stick to it. Is this insubordination?

180
00:11:04,844 --> 00:11:06,864
It's not insubordination,

181
00:11:06,888 --> 00:11:09,286
it's just... I want to be seen as
a good man rather than a good junior.

182
00:11:09,310 --> 00:11:10,287
It's insubordination.

183
00:11:10,311 --> 00:11:13,836
Rules are meant to be broken,
and promises are meant to be bent.

184
00:11:13,860 --> 00:11:14,936
Why are you talking back?

185
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,980
If you don't cross the line, it's fine.

186
00:11:18,266 --> 00:11:19,856
Lines exist to be crossed!

187
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,822
They exist to be kept.

188
00:11:25,420 --> 00:11:28,020
We'll get going then.

189
00:11:28,044 --> 00:11:30,506
Geu Rin, we'll get going then.

190
00:11:30,530 --> 00:11:36,598
Stop hitting on him! See
you tomorrow. Come on.

191
00:11:36,622 --> 00:11:38,760
Bye.

192
00:11:39,955 --> 00:11:43,288
You two look good together.

193
00:11:45,155 --> 00:11:48,186
- Let's go.
- Koo Seon Ho, go home.

194
00:11:48,210 --> 00:11:50,287
If you take me home first,
you have to go all the way back.

195
00:11:50,311 --> 00:11:54,756
- Go. Don't be weird.
- It's still early. I haven't even had a drink.

196
00:11:54,780 --> 00:11:58,533
Only transform into my private jet
when I'm black-out drunk.

197
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,926
Jeez, so awkward.

198
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:08,356
Don't be so serious. What about my limbs?

199
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:11,376
Hey!

200
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,526
I'm doing this so I'll feel less
sorry to your future wife.

201
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:15,856
What if I send you to her with worn-out
bones from doing all the work?

202
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:19,777
If you can't use your strength when you need
to, I'll become your family's sworn enemy.

203
00:12:23,866 --> 00:12:26,177
Stop it.

204
00:12:29,777 --> 00:12:31,353
Bye.

205
00:12:31,377 --> 00:12:34,956
Oh right, what's this week's concept?

206
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:38,622
Bye, my friend Koo Seon
Ho. See you tomorrow.

207
00:12:45,530 --> 00:12:46,916
What should this week's concept be?

208
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:48,196
Suggestions are welcome!

209
00:12:48,220 --> 00:12:49,220
- The King's Woman.
- Book Club.

210
00:12:49,244 --> 00:12:50,376
- In Search of a Poet.
- Mental Anguish.

211
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,846
- Here We Go Again.
- Gone With the Wind.

212
00:12:51,870 --> 00:12:53,042
No comments.

213
00:12:53,066 --> 00:12:55,008
This is fun.

214
00:12:59,422 --> 00:13:02,566
But why isn't Seon Ho saying anything?

215
00:13:02,590 --> 00:13:05,377
Why isn't Baeblu saying anything?

216
00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:10,696
I'll just go with whatever's decided.

217
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:13,316
That's not how it works. Unacceptable.

218
00:13:13,340 --> 00:13:15,306
Let's pick a penalty.
This time Baeblu decides.

219
00:13:15,330 --> 00:13:19,777
Huh? Me?

220
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:22,906
It's Baeblu's turn.

221
00:13:22,930 --> 00:13:29,511
Baeblu! Baeblu! Baeblu! Baeblu!

222
00:13:36,928 --> 00:13:41,422
Hey! Nam Gi Jeong! No input?
Why are you just lurking?

223
00:13:43,111 --> 00:13:46,177
Gi Jeong isn't saying anything, either.

224
00:13:55,730 --> 00:13:58,636
Yes...

225
00:13:58,660 --> 00:14:00,776
They're practically
invisible. So transparent.

226
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:03,155
What? What's this?

227
00:14:04,755 --> 00:14:06,933
Wait, I need to focus.

228
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:12,888
Hey, can you talk right now?

229
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:18,776
So transparent, right?

230
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:25,066
- What? Where's he going?
- Nice! Where's he headed?

231
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:30,909
- Gi Jeong.
- What? What?

232
00:14:30,933 --> 00:14:32,516
You saw SF's group chat, right?

233
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:36,556
The crucial task of deciding
this week's concept fell on me.

234
00:14:36,580 --> 00:14:39,236
What's so important about that?

235
00:14:39,260 --> 00:14:42,376
Are you entering the Biennale or something?

236
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:45,526
Or walking the Academy's red carpet?

237
00:14:45,550 --> 00:14:49,036
Maybe directing a Grammy stage?

238
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:53,931
It's just that I've never taken
the lead on anything before.

239
00:14:53,955 --> 00:14:58,533
- Hey, you...
- That's not it. I'm afraid I'll disappoint everyone.

240
00:14:59,150 --> 00:15:01,066
What if everyone hates it?

241
00:15:01,090 --> 00:15:03,756
What if they pretend to
like it when they don't?

242
00:15:03,780 --> 00:15:05,931
- That would be a nuisance, wouldn't it?
- You dummy.

243
00:15:05,955 --> 00:15:08,356
How is that a nuisance?

244
00:15:08,380 --> 00:15:12,064
Hey, then just make the concept
'Things That Suck.'

245
00:15:12,088 --> 00:15:15,016
- Problem solved. The worse, the better.
- Huh?

246
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:18,946
Everyone will scramble to come dressed
as the worst thing they can think of.

247
00:15:18,970 --> 00:15:21,826
Look at Green Pig.

248
00:15:21,850 --> 00:15:24,876
Are there any normal people in that group
who would be disappointed?

249
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:27,396
- Ah...
- What 'ah'?

250
00:15:27,420 --> 00:15:30,896
Why are you always so
anxious about everything?

251
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:33,377
Just go for it. Anything.

252
00:15:34,355 --> 00:15:36,546
- This is why I called.
- What?

253
00:15:36,570 --> 00:15:39,556
I told you why I wanted to talk.

254
00:15:39,580 --> 00:15:42,577
Talking to you makes everything easier.

255
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:48,076
I feel stronger talking to you.
There is no logical reason,

256
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:54,198
but you're a miracle. Thanks.

257
00:15:54,222 --> 00:15:56,577
You helped me decide what to do.

258
00:15:57,333 --> 00:16:00,326
Got it. Bye.

259
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:03,288
- Gi Jeong!
- What? What?

260
00:16:04,222 --> 00:16:06,266
Are you really not mad?

261
00:16:14,044 --> 00:16:19,022
You don't actually like Seon Ho, right?

262
00:16:19,955 --> 00:16:23,887
- Shut up.
- No.

263
00:16:23,911 --> 00:16:28,090
Fine. I'm not mad, either. Bye.

264
00:16:34,533 --> 00:16:37,511
I finally moved on. Why bring it up again?

265
00:16:45,950 --> 00:16:49,088
- About what? Huh?
- Gosh!

266
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:53,406
Who likes Seon Ho?

267
00:16:53,430 --> 00:16:55,036
Wait, who's Seon Ho?

268
00:16:55,060 --> 00:16:56,037
Geu Rin's friend,

269
00:16:56,061 --> 00:16:57,796
from the drawing club.

270
00:16:57,820 --> 00:17:00,166
Him? Who likes him?

271
00:17:00,190 --> 00:17:03,746
Miss Piggy? That Miss Piggy likes him?

272
00:17:03,770 --> 00:17:07,309
So that's why you're upset?

273
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:10,846
My sister. I'm talking about Green Pig.

274
00:17:10,870 --> 00:17:13,866
Nam Geu Rin likes Seon Ho.

275
00:17:14,755 --> 00:17:18,036
Okay. That's possible.

276
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:21,155
But why are you upset?

277
00:17:22,444 --> 00:17:25,487
I'm her younger brother!

278
00:17:25,511 --> 00:17:28,436
So, I'd surely feel a little bad,
and it could be that.

279
00:17:28,460 --> 00:17:31,066
Think about it, guys.

280
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:37,511
Do you like Seon Ho? Seriously?

281
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:40,776
So that's why you were upset.

282
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:42,776
No! Really! Stop it!

283
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,487
We're friends! I mean it.

284
00:17:45,511 --> 00:17:47,309
Don't call us friends!

285
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,555
Don't come near me!

286
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:54,577
My concept is

287
00:17:57,288 --> 00:18:00,355
something I've never tried my whole life.

288
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:05,264
And probably never will.

289
00:18:05,288 --> 00:18:08,177
Because I'd definitely fail.

290
00:18:10,444 --> 00:18:17,887
♫ G.O.A.T. G.O.A.T. ♫

291
00:18:17,911 --> 00:18:22,106
Let's try it once before I die, 'girl crush'.

292
00:18:22,130 --> 00:18:25,846
♫ I'm the bottom line ♫

293
00:18:25,870 --> 00:18:27,620
♫ I'ma make my moves ♫

294
00:18:27,644 --> 00:18:28,706
♫ Better hurry up ♫

295
00:18:28,730 --> 00:18:31,626
♫ What you waiting for ♫

296
00:18:31,650 --> 00:18:34,360
♫ I'm your go-to ♫

297
00:18:35,466 --> 00:18:38,844
- Baeblu!
- Hello.

298
00:18:40,444 --> 00:18:44,533
- Ready to transform, Baeblu?
- Yes.

299
00:18:46,222 --> 00:18:48,553
This is totally U Yeon's style. U Yeon!

300
00:18:48,577 --> 00:18:50,686
This is so hip. So cool.

301
00:18:50,710 --> 00:18:53,422
- How about this?
- This looks better.

302
00:19:02,577 --> 00:19:04,480
Not this? What then?

303
00:19:25,644 --> 00:19:28,716
It's a 'girl crush' concept.

304
00:19:28,740 --> 00:19:31,100
But why does she look cute in everything?

305
00:19:37,555 --> 00:19:40,400
Wait. Let me try something.

306
00:19:41,422 --> 00:19:46,106
Ta-da! Looks perfect. Right?

307
00:19:46,130 --> 00:19:47,906
I've never tried this hairstyle before.

308
00:19:47,930 --> 00:19:49,776
I think it's good.

309
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:53,066
Wait, there's an outfit I
had my eye on. Hold on.

310
00:19:53,090 --> 00:19:54,977
I also picked something out.

311
00:20:11,822 --> 00:20:15,777
To be honest, I've never
really gone shopping properly.

312
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:27,036
- Ta-da! How do I look?
- Hmm, pretty and cute.

313
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:31,106
Even when shopping with friends,
I'd end up empty-handed.

314
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:33,220
It always ended with me
just agreeing with them.

315
00:20:33,244 --> 00:20:35,866
Song, aren't you buying anything?

316
00:20:35,890 --> 00:20:38,844
You said that was pretty. At least try it on.

317
00:20:44,380 --> 00:20:46,109
Even if I saw clothes I liked...

318
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:50,046
No, it probably won't look good on me.

319
00:20:50,070 --> 00:20:54,711
So I always bought clothes that
were unnoticeable, just like me.

320
00:20:57,822 --> 00:20:59,955
Why? Do you like that?

321
00:21:00,610 --> 00:21:03,036
I just thought it looked nice.

322
00:21:03,060 --> 00:21:06,206
- I've wanted to try this style.
- Then, try it.

323
00:21:06,230 --> 00:21:08,331
You have to try clothes on to know.

324
00:21:08,355 --> 00:21:12,177
- No, I've never worn clothes like this...
- We'll try this.

325
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:27,456
- Does it look weird?
- No, not at all.

326
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,280
You like it?

327
00:21:31,940 --> 00:21:34,886
- Yes! Totally.
- Then it's settled.

328
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:37,186
- Shopping done. She'll wear this.
- Wait a moment.

329
00:21:37,210 --> 00:21:40,109
Why? Is there a problem?

330
00:21:40,133 --> 00:21:42,596
I was wondering if I should
buy something more plain.

331
00:21:42,620 --> 00:21:45,042
I probably won't wear it much anyway.

332
00:21:45,066 --> 00:21:46,696
Are you from the future?

333
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:49,046
Giving up in advance? That's a bad habit.

334
00:21:49,070 --> 00:21:53,346
So what? Just wear it once. Let's go!

335
00:21:53,370 --> 00:21:55,716
Why are you always so
anxious about everything?

336
00:21:55,740 --> 00:21:58,086
Just go for it.

337
00:21:58,110 --> 00:22:01,466
Then I'll leave wearing this.

338
00:22:06,844 --> 00:22:11,006
Wow, look how pretty
they are. Are they models?

339
00:22:11,030 --> 00:22:13,446
Whoa, so stunning.

340
00:22:13,470 --> 00:22:17,955
Hey, isn't that the loser girl?

341
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:21,333
Huh? No way.

342
00:22:25,090 --> 00:22:26,406
That's great.

343
00:22:26,430 --> 00:22:30,126
If she was alone, I'd totally
shake her down. Forget it.

344
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:31,726
No word from Ahn Ye Rim?

345
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:33,264
Is she coming today or not?

346
00:22:33,288 --> 00:22:37,155
Gosh! I just got a text. She can't make it.

347
00:22:41,555 --> 00:22:44,744
Jeez, so annoying. She
made us wait all this time.

348
00:22:44,768 --> 00:22:47,420
Okay. Next pose.

349
00:22:48,790 --> 00:22:51,111
Let's try crossing arms gently.

350
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:55,726
Let's take a short break.

351
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:57,556
We barely shot anything! Break already?

352
00:22:57,580 --> 00:22:59,106
Let's just power through.

353
00:22:59,130 --> 00:23:00,396
- Faster.
- Just a short break.

354
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:02,642
Ye Rim isn't even complaining.

355
00:23:02,666 --> 00:23:04,196
It's hot. Let's rest for
five minutes. Seriously.

356
00:23:04,220 --> 00:23:06,664
Hey, the boss is talking here.

357
00:23:06,688 --> 00:23:08,996
Aren't you coming? Coming or not?

358
00:23:09,020 --> 00:23:10,796
I'll go drag him here.

359
00:23:10,820 --> 00:23:12,706
Let's just rest for five more minutes.

360
00:23:12,730 --> 00:23:14,366
We've got plenty of time.

361
00:23:14,390 --> 00:23:18,044
Fine. Let's rest.

362
00:23:27,140 --> 00:23:29,900
[Oh! You met U Yeon?]

363
00:23:35,511 --> 00:23:38,622
Man, this weather's insane.

364
00:23:42,304 --> 00:23:47,220
- Why no progress in your crush?
- Stop it.

365
00:23:47,244 --> 00:23:50,509
- Siblings fighting over one guy?
- Ridiculous.

366
00:23:50,533 --> 00:23:52,696
- My heart aches.
- Aches indeed.

367
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:55,398
- This is boring.
- It's fun! Really!

368
00:23:55,422 --> 00:23:58,196
But you know, Seon Ho and Geu Rin
have been close for a long time.

369
00:23:58,220 --> 00:24:00,776
They've been friends since middle school.

370
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:03,976
Where do you fit between them?

371
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,976
You haven't confessed yet, right?

372
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:11,256
Don't confess! Just don't. Please.

373
00:24:11,280 --> 00:24:16,088
If you do that and get rejected hard, you'll be
banging your head in the closet again screaming.

374
00:24:18,580 --> 00:24:21,288
- Did you actually confess?
- Jeez, you scared me.

375
00:24:22,755 --> 00:24:25,866
Are you going to keep doing
this? It's not even funny.

376
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,886
What's not fun?

377
00:24:28,910 --> 00:24:31,377
Gi Jeong likes some guy.

378
00:24:32,888 --> 00:24:35,822
- Tae Seon, Dae O, come here.
- Yes?

379
00:24:45,030 --> 00:24:47,516
Is your phone broken?

380
00:24:47,540 --> 00:24:52,336
No. Stop sending me selfies.

381
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:53,526
Because you're not replying.

382
00:24:53,550 --> 00:24:57,186
I keep asking if I look
good, and you ignore me.

383
00:24:57,210 --> 00:24:59,896
- Why won't you reply?
- Why are you asking me that?

384
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:02,177
You'd know if you looked in the mirror.

385
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:06,577
I want to hear it from you, that's all.

386
00:25:10,266 --> 00:25:14,711
- How many outfits left?
- Five. Why?

387
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:19,131
I'll finish them in thirty minutes.

388
00:25:19,155 --> 00:25:22,786
You'll finish? Oh wow, Mr. Hotshot
here. Who do you think you are?

389
00:25:22,810 --> 00:25:23,926
I'll do as instructed.

390
00:25:23,950 --> 00:25:26,356
Whether it's linking arms or putting
an arm around the shoulder, I'll do it all.

391
00:25:26,380 --> 00:25:29,806
I can even do a pose that's
stronger than what you want.

392
00:25:29,830 --> 00:25:32,444
Nice! Next pose!

393
00:25:34,304 --> 00:25:36,512
Okay.

394
00:25:39,730 --> 00:25:41,866
Oh, this works.

395
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:47,644
Good. More! Just a bit more.

396
00:25:49,911 --> 00:25:51,516
Okay, got it!

397
00:25:51,540 --> 00:25:54,109
Got the shot. We're wrapping up.

398
00:25:54,133 --> 00:25:56,940
Done? Are we finished? Bye.

399
00:25:57,644 --> 00:26:00,306
- Hey! Change first.
- I'm late.

400
00:26:00,330 --> 00:26:02,355
Hey, where are you going?

401
00:26:03,511 --> 00:26:05,511
What's the rush?

402
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:23,216
Pretty. The pink
hairpiece makes it perfect.

403
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:25,176
Really?

404
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:28,872
We're done here. We'll go ahead.

405
00:26:28,896 --> 00:26:31,288
We'll go finish up.

406
00:26:37,066 --> 00:26:39,626
♫ You've waited so long, I'm late ♫

407
00:26:39,650 --> 00:26:44,516
♫ I'm sorry, I'm new to this, didn't know ♫

408
00:26:44,540 --> 00:26:47,753
♫ Just because it's you,
just because I like you ♫

409
00:26:47,777 --> 00:26:52,766
♫ Words can't express it ♫

410
00:26:52,790 --> 00:26:53,776
Nam Gi Jeong?

411
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:56,355
♫ There's no other way ♫

412
00:26:57,422 --> 00:26:59,902
You said you couldn't come today
because of your part-time job.

413
00:27:01,866 --> 00:27:05,170
♫ I've captured it all here ♫

414
00:27:14,088 --> 00:27:15,911
It ended earlier.

415
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:17,977
The 'screwed' concept, how is it?

416
00:27:18,001 --> 00:27:20,000
The 'things that suck' concept.

417
00:27:20,622 --> 00:27:23,656
What kind of 'things
that suck' concept is this?

418
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:28,800
What's more 'sucky' for me than 'girl
crush'? How is it? Full of concept, right?

419
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:34,577
- I don't know.
- You came? I thought you couldn't make it.

420
00:27:36,970 --> 00:27:39,976
Why is that guy coming
down from there again?

421
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:44,000
- Hello.
- Doesn't U Yeon and I have similar vibes today?

422
00:27:45,022 --> 00:27:46,776
It looks good on you.

423
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:50,256
Really? The girls helped me get ready.

424
00:27:50,280 --> 00:27:52,236
Let's go, Miss Piggy.

425
00:27:52,260 --> 00:27:53,346
Let's go, huh?

426
00:27:53,370 --> 00:27:57,664
Where? Is it here today? Here?

427
00:27:57,688 --> 00:27:59,620
Oh, it's here.

428
00:28:02,208 --> 00:28:03,531
Why are you annoyed?

429
00:28:03,555 --> 00:28:06,088
It actually suits her surprisingly well.

430
00:28:06,790 --> 00:28:08,700
Who does it suit?

431
00:28:09,370 --> 00:28:11,911
You should make some
noise when you move around.

432
00:28:12,844 --> 00:28:15,646
How do I look today? Isn't it amazing?

433
00:28:15,670 --> 00:28:18,910
Wow, it's really amazing.

434
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:29,220
Put this on.

435
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:37,346
Hey! What are you doing?
This is part of the concept.

436
00:28:37,370 --> 00:28:40,577
You'll catch a cold. Give it to me
when we're working later.

437
00:28:52,133 --> 00:28:53,955
Looks like you're getting hit again today.

438
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:59,644
Alright, shall we begin?

439
00:29:06,666 --> 00:29:08,731
Hey! Move aside.

440
00:29:08,755 --> 00:29:10,446
This is my spot, okay?

441
00:29:10,470 --> 00:29:12,296
Out. Get out.

442
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:15,260
Hey, I saved this spot with my sketchbook.

443
00:29:38,177 --> 00:29:40,936
♫ You're shining brightly ♫

444
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:47,436
♫ Like a star lighting up my heart ♫

445
00:29:47,460 --> 00:29:52,598
♫ With your own light, your own colors ♫

446
00:29:52,622 --> 00:29:59,520
♫ Filling the whole world
and my dreams with beauty ♫

447
00:30:09,060 --> 00:30:10,933
My pencil is broken.

448
00:30:13,180 --> 00:30:14,836
Pass me a pencil.

449
00:30:14,860 --> 00:30:17,190
Hey, I'm using this.

450
00:30:22,577 --> 00:30:24,640
Okay, one minute left.

451
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:29,466
This one is a masterpiece. A masterpiece!

452
00:30:29,490 --> 00:30:32,044
I loved the cosplay theme.

453
00:30:34,100 --> 00:30:36,064
Look, look!

454
00:30:36,088 --> 00:30:38,350
But where is Baeblu's drawing?

455
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:43,111
Why are you like this?

456
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:48,836
Let me see.

457
00:30:48,860 --> 00:30:50,926
I really messed up drawing this.

458
00:30:50,950 --> 00:30:53,006
It's okay. It's okay.

459
00:30:53,030 --> 00:30:54,326
No, it's not okay.

460
00:30:54,350 --> 00:30:59,955
It's only been a short time, of course. Plus
I told you it doesn't matter if it's bad.

461
00:31:10,144 --> 00:31:12,000
Is this me?

462
00:31:12,755 --> 00:31:14,642
What's wrong with you, Green Pig?

463
00:31:14,666 --> 00:31:17,410
You need to be re-educated!

464
00:31:26,977 --> 00:31:32,888
Listen up, Baeblu. Confidence
matters more than skill. Got it?

465
00:31:34,300 --> 00:31:36,240
Let's go.

466
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,844
Gather around.

467
00:31:39,550 --> 00:31:42,400
- It's enough.
- Okay, stop.

468
00:31:43,500 --> 00:31:45,377
Let me see.

469
00:31:49,060 --> 00:31:51,777
The lines have such energy.

470
00:31:55,350 --> 00:31:58,476
Hmm, you're surprisingly a power-type.

471
00:31:58,500 --> 00:32:02,166
- You're 'gentle on the outside, strong on the inside'?
- What did you say?

472
00:32:02,190 --> 00:32:03,167
The sense of proportion is good.

473
00:32:03,191 --> 00:32:06,806
It's really amazing for someone
who hasn't been doing it long.

474
00:32:06,830 --> 00:32:09,416
Your chaotic inner self
is expressed perfectly.

475
00:32:09,440 --> 00:32:12,090
As expected of the stormy
period of adolescence.

476
00:32:13,111 --> 00:32:15,822
- Stormy, stormy...
- You're going to be great.

477
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:17,696
There's no way...

478
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:20,956
There's just no way. No, really,

479
00:32:20,980 --> 00:32:24,598
what's wrong with everyone's eyes?
What about this... where?

480
00:32:24,622 --> 00:32:26,864
It's hard to even draw like this
when it's your first time.

481
00:32:26,888 --> 00:32:30,198
It's good. It's good for a first time.

482
00:32:30,222 --> 00:32:32,856
You still haven't been hit
enough! You! Get back here!

483
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:35,410
What's your problem, Green Pig?

484
00:32:42,222 --> 00:32:44,133
Geu Rin is right.

485
00:32:46,311 --> 00:32:47,996
That's good for your level, Baeblu.

486
00:32:48,020 --> 00:32:50,716
I couldn't even draw a
single line for a month.

487
00:32:50,740 --> 00:32:52,540
Should I show you?

488
00:32:57,580 --> 00:33:01,422
Ah, here.

489
00:33:04,050 --> 00:33:06,976
And today...

490
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:08,796
Today, you even colored?

491
00:33:08,820 --> 00:33:13,155
- I had 2 seconds left, so I tried coloring.
- Coloring?

492
00:33:16,355 --> 00:33:17,896
I still think my strokes are too light.

493
00:33:17,920 --> 00:33:20,533
Still better than me.

494
00:33:22,266 --> 00:33:26,316
Yeah, I can't even finish mine.
I always leave off an arm or a leg.

495
00:33:26,340 --> 00:33:29,586
But you're really good at drawing faces.

496
00:33:29,610 --> 00:33:33,356
I find drawing faces really fun.

497
00:33:33,380 --> 00:33:37,066
Look. Especially the expressions.
They're all different, right?

498
00:33:37,090 --> 00:33:42,706
If I look at them closely, I get really
focused, and... it's just so much fun.

499
00:33:42,730 --> 00:33:46,736
So, Khaki, take off that hat sometimes.

500
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:49,596
Right, let's see your face.

501
00:33:49,620 --> 00:33:53,111
Everyone really loves drawing.

502
00:33:54,088 --> 00:33:56,686
Hey, is this you?

503
00:33:56,710 --> 00:33:58,406
You said this was a
group for people who draw.

504
00:33:58,430 --> 00:33:59,798
What is this?

505
00:33:59,822 --> 00:34:07,155
How could they laugh at a drawing someone
worked so hard on? That's the worst.

506
00:34:08,350 --> 00:34:10,687
It's no different from that jerk.

507
00:34:10,711 --> 00:34:14,509
Okay, let's finish with a couple
pose. Who wants to do it?

508
